metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #119
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

metadata.name: Strokes on Tezos by gmi.sh #19
metadata.description:
The derivative collection of strokes.gmi.sh – the original, the first on-chain abstract art collection by gmi.sh. Each Stroke is defined on ꜩ blockchain, the assets are stored on IPFS and rendered through fxhash contract. 

This collection is re-using the original CC0 assets of Strokes by gmi.sh on Etherium.

Please note: the original Strokes are kinetic and evolve over time, Strokes on Tezos are static.

metadata.name: twofiftythousand #50
metadata.description:
twofiftythousand is about the chaos of unlimited decisions. Look for a pattern in the noise.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific pixel width (default = browser sized). This will be dependent on your system specifications, but outputs of up to 8000px wide, or above, should be possible.
